Test-case name:XFCE4 Window Manager

This test will check that Window Manager opens and closes correctly
<dl>
    <dt>Open Window Manager from Settings dialogue</dt>
	<dd>Window Manager opens to Style tab</dd>
    <dt>Press X in top right corner of window manager</dt>
	<dd>Window Manager closes</dd>
</dl>
This test will check that Themes are applied correctly
<dl>
    <dt>Open Window Manager from Settings dialogue</dt>
	<dd>Window Manager opens to Style tab, theme set to default</dd>
    <dt>Change theme</dt>
	<dd>Window theme changes to new style</dd>
    <dt>Change theme back to default</dt>
	<dd>Default theme is applied</dd>
</dl>
This test will check that Window title and button customisation's are applied correctly
    <dt>Change Title font from default</dt>
	<dd>Window title font changes</dd>
    <dt>Change Title alignment from default</dt>
	<dd>Title alignment changes</dd>
    <dt>Change Title font and alignment back to default</dt>
	<dd>Title font and alignment change</dd>
    <dt>Click and drag buttons in Button layout</dt>
	<dd>Buttons move in Window title bar</dd>
    <dt>Return buttons to default position</dt>
	<dd>Buttons return to default positions</dd>
    <dt>Move an Active button to the Hidden area</dt>
	<dd>Button disappears from Window title bar</dd>
    <dt>Move button from Hidden area to Active</dt>
	<dd>Button appears in Window title bar</dd>
    <dt>Return buttons to default positions</dt>
	<dd>Buttons return to default positions</dd>
</dl>
This test will check that Focus changes are applied correctly
<dl>
    <dt>Select Focus Tab</dt>
	<dd>Window changes to Focus tab, Click to focus, New window focus, Raise on click selected by default</dd> 
    <dt>Select Focus follows mouse</dt>
	<dd>Focus follow mouse button selected</dd>
    <dt>Open any other application</dt>
	<dd>Chosen application opens</dd>
    <dt>Move between application windows without clicking</dt>
	<dd>Focus moves between applications following mouse</dd>
    <dt>Move Focus delay slider</dt>
	<dd>Speed at which focus is applied changes</dd>
    <dt>Deselect all focus options, leaving focus model at Click to focus</dt>
	<dd>All ticks removed from boxes</dd>
    <dt>Open a terminal with Super +T</dt>
	<dd>Terminal opens, focus stays with Window Manager</dd>
	<dd>Window Manager is not raised above Terminal</dd>
    <dt>Click Window Manager title bar</dt>
	<dd>Window Manager is raised</dd>
    <dt>Select Raise on click</dt>
	<dd>Tick appears in box</dd>
    <dt>Click inside Terminal</dt>
	<dd>Terminal gains focus and is raised above other windows</dd>
    <dt>Deselect Raise on click, select Raise on focus</dt>
	<dd>Tick appears in Raise on focus, removed from Raise on click</dd>
    <dt>Click in terminal</dt>
	<dd>Terminal gains focus</dd>
    <dt>Deselect Raise on focus, select New Window focus</dt>
	<dd>Tick appears in New window focus, tick removed from Raise on focus</dd>
    <dt>Open terminal</dt>
	<dd>Terminal opens raised and with focus</dd>
    <dt>Reset settings to default</dt>
	<dd>Ticks appear in New window focus and Raise on Click</dd>
</dl>
This test will check that Advanced options are applied correctly
    <dt>Select Advanced tab</dt>
	<dd>Window changes to advanced tab, Snap windows to screen border and Wrap workspaces when dragging selected by default</dd>







   

